<TITLE> Blonska stripped of heptathlon silver for doping </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BEIJING, Aug 22 (bdnews24.com) Ukrainian athlete Lyudmila Blonska, who won a silver in heptathlon was stripped of her medal Friday, the International Olympic Committee said. Blonska was tested positive for the steroid methyltestosterone after finishing second in the heptathlon last Saturday. She was temporarily suspended by the IOC after the backup "B" sample also came back positive Thursday, and the IOC executive board Friday officially removed her medal. The Ukrainian Olympic committee was ordered to return Blonska's medal "as soon as possible." The 30-year-old Ukrainian faces a lifetime ban for a second doping offense. She was suspended from 2003-05 for using the steroid stanozolo
